Sportsdigita is an American sports technology firm headquartered in Minneapolis, Minnesota. It was founded in 2011 by Angelina Lawton, former head of corporate communications for the Tampa Bay Lightning and winner of the Minneapolis/St. Paul Business Journal's 2017 Women in Business Award. Angelina is the wife of former professional hockey player, agent, manager and current on-air analyst for the NHL Network, Brian Lawton. Sportsdigita is the creator of the Digideck online presentation tool.
In 2015 entrepreneur and technology leader Cory Factor joined Sportsdigita as President. Factor is the former CEO of MinuteBids and a 2013 Minneapolis/St. Paul Business Journal 40 under 40 honoree.
